REIGER PARK - Reiger Park residents have taken to the streets over the allocation of RDP houses.They say they won t stop their protests until they get answers from the Ekurhuleni Municipality.In February, the municipality launched the Leeuwpoort housing project.READ: Reiger Park residents demand housesThe multi-billion rand partially-subsidised social housing development stands to benefit informal settlement dwellers from surrounding areas like Jo Slovo, Vosloorus and Katlehong.But Reiger Park residents says they won t benefit.Reiger Park community leader Leon Rooi said they want the MMC to involve all the so-called coloured communities in Ekurhuleni to make them first priority of the project.eNCA